TITLE: seyfert.config.mjs (HTTP Bot)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet configures Seyfert for an HTTP-based bot using the `config.http` function.  It sets the bot token, application ID, public key, file locations for commands, and port. All required environment variables must be set for the application to work. `locations.base` indicates the root directory, and `locations.commands` where the bot command files are.
SOURCE: https://github.com/tiramisulabs/seyfert-docs/blob/main/src/content/docs/getting-started/setup-project.mdx#_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
// This is not shown, prevents errors.
process.env.BOT_APP_ID = '';
process.env.BOT_PUBLIC_KEY = '';
process.env.BOT_TOKEN = '';
// ---cut---
import { config } from "seyfert";

const  {
    BOT_TOKEN, BOT_APP_ID, BOT_PUBLIC_KEY
} = process.env;

export default config.http({
    token: BOT_TOKEN,
    locations: {
        base: "dist", // replace with "src" if using bun
        commands: "commands"
    },
    applicationId: BOT_APP_ID,
    port: 3000, // default is 8080
    publicKey: BOT_PUBLIC_KEY
});
```

