TITLE: Creating a Subcommand in Seyfert (TypeScript)
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet shows how to create a subcommand using the `SubCommand` class from 'seyfert'.  The `@Declare` decorator sets the subcommand's name and description. The `run` method is implemented to define the subcommand's logic, taking a `CommandContext` object as input and returning a `ctx.write` promise.
SOURCE: https://github.com/tiramisulabs/seyfert-docs/blob/main/src/content/docs/commands/subcommands.mdx#_snippet_1

