TITLE: Using Defer Reply in a Prefix Command
DESCRIPTION: This code shows how to use `ctx.deferReply()` in a prefix command. Coupled with the above configuration, the command's response will be deferred, and the specified message will be shown while the command is being processed. After the processing (crossposting), a final confirmation message is sent.
SOURCE: https://github.com/tiramisulabs/seyfert-docs/blob/main/src/content/docs/commands/prefix-commands.mdx#_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import {
    Command,
    CommandContext,
    Declare,
    Options,
    createStringOption
} from 'seyfert';

const options = {
    id: createStringOption({
        description: 'The ID of the message we are going to crosspost',
        required: true
    })
};

@Declare({
    name: 'crosspost',
    description: 'Crosspost an announcement message.'
})
@Options(options)
export default class CrosspostCommand extends Command {
    async run(ctx: CommandContext<typeof options>){
        await ctx.deferReply();
        await ctx.client.messages.crosspost(ctx.options.id, ctx.channelId);
        return ctx.write({ content: 'I have crossposted your announcement.'});
    }
};
```

