TITLE: Stopping Middleware Execution with an Error (TypeScript)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet illustrates how to stop the execution of a Seyfert command's middleware chain by returning a `stop` result. This allows certain conditions to halt a command's execution early, preventing it from running if unmet. The `stop` function takes a string argument which represents the error message.
SOURCE: https://github.com/tiramisulabs/seyfert-docs/blob/main/src/content/docs/es/commands/handling-errors.md#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const Devs = [''];
// ---cut---
import { createMiddleware } from "seyfert";

export default createMiddleware<void>(({ context, next, stop, pass }) => {
    if (!Devs.includes(context.author.id)) {
        return stop("El usuario no es un desarrollador");
    }
    next();
});
```

